description: This grooving bit features an ogee profile and a 1-1/4" cutting diameter which is perfect for the rail and stile section of a CNC faux panel door profile. This bit has a total cutting depth of 1/2" and a 1/2" shank. Making cabinet doors on a CNC machine can result in beautiful and flawless doors in minutes without the hassle of cutting multiple pieces of stock, fitting and gluing and all the issues that can arise. Yonico manufactures a full line of CNC cabinet door rail and stile bits with profiles that are meant to mimic authentic rail and stile frames.
